"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
                             Computer Code Corresponding to:

                           Fitting Structural Equation Models 
                             via Variational Approximations       

                             by K.-D. Dang and L. Maestrini

                               Last changed: 26 NOV 2021.

"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""

   The R script SEMfit.R fits a Bayesian structural equation model to a subset of the
Holzinger and Swineford (1939). A single latent factor (visual ability) is considered. 
The credible intervals obtained via mean field variational Bayes can be compared with 
those of Markov chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) and MFVB paired with (percentile and pivotal) 
bootstrap. The thick grey lines in the plots are MCMC credible intervals. The black 
lines correspond to credible intervals from MFVB or MFVB plus bootstrap.

   The script SEMfit.R is supported by files containing functions. These files are 
summarised in the following table. 


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
          file name                               description 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MFVBforSEM.r                      R function for fitting the model via MFVB.

MCMCforSEM.r                      Stan function for fitting the model via MCMC.

SEMfit.R                          Main R script for fitting the structural equation via
                                  MFVB and MCMC, and performing bootstrap.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


